    <h1 class="essay-title">What is MoodSpoon</h1>
  </header>

  <div class="essay-body">
  <p>My name is Peter. I'm a facilitator and group moderator. For 20 years, I've held space for people in workshops and groups. Listening, asking questions, watching how people change when they feel heard. That taught me something: everyone is struggling with something. The only difference is which demons you're learning to live with.</p>
 
  <p>I wrote these essays because I believe we don't need more advice. We need breadcrumbs. Small thoughts about rest, presence, exhaustion and what it means to show up as yourself. Even when showing up feels impossible.</p>
 
  <p>These are notes from someone in the struggle, not someone above it. My hope is simple: that you'll recognize yourself in these pages, feel a little less alone and perhaps find one small thing that helps you cope, move forward or smile more easily.</p>
 
  <p>The goal is to help you be more confident in the person you already are. And to help you live with your demons a little more gracefully.</p>
